51
00:04:58,600 --> 00:05:06,650
FREE WILLY

52
00:05:11,450 --> 00:05:14,300
Excuse me. My mom dropped me off
on the way to work,

53
00:05:14,300 --> 00:05:15,500
And she forgot
to give me bus fare.

54
00:05:15,700 --> 00:05:17,300
Could I borrow
some money?

55
00:05:20,140 --> 00:05:21,750
Oh, thanks, lady!
You have a good day.

56
00:05:21,750 --> 00:05:22,400
Thanks a lot!

57
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:23,500
I really gotta get home, man.

58
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:24,500
If you could lend me
a just, like, a buck--

59
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:25,650
Get outta here.

60
00:05:27,350 --> 00:05:28,750
Excuse me, lady.
Excuse me.

61
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,500
My friends and I
are having a problem.

62
00:05:30,500 --> 00:05:32,500
You see, we spent all our money
at the natural history museum,

63
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:33,850
And we have to take
the ferry home.

64
00:05:33,850 --> 00:05:35,000
Think you could
help me out?

65
00:05:36,490 --> 00:05:37,660
I suppose.

66
00:05:41,700 --> 00:05:43,400
A few bucks.

67
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:45,400
Shoot!
I'm hungry.

68
00:05:45,850 --> 00:05:47,750
God, man.
I need some food.

69
00:05:58,850 --> 00:06:00,250
Let's go.

70
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:09,000
Let's go, Jess!

71
00:06:11,700 --> 00:06:13,550
Hey! Hey, you kids!

72
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:14,900
Come back here!

73
00:06:37,300 --> 00:06:38,400
Ha ha ha!

74
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:40,230
Oh, cool!

75
00:06:40,230 --> 00:06:42,460
Yeah!
Come on, guys.

76
00:06:43,460 --> 00:06:44,900
Wha ha!

77
00:06:45,450 --> 00:06:46,630
Whoo!

78
00:06:47,900 --> 00:06:50,800
You know, the first time
I ever went there,

79
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:52,300
oh!  It was so bad.

80
00:06:52,500 --> 00:06:55,000
My mom dropped me off when
she went to work in Houston.

81
00:06:55,100 --> 00:06:56,600
I never saw her again.

82
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:59,000
I Don't care.
I hate her anyway.

83
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:01,250
You know, I could eat
one of these every day.

84
00:07:01,250 --> 00:07:02,720
Yeah,
well, I bolted.

85
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:06,400
- Oh!  You bolted from Cooperton?
- I did, bonehead.

86
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:07,850
Yeah, right.

87
00:07:07,850 --> 00:07:10,300
Shut up! Bull shit!
What do you know?

88
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:13,350
I know they watch like you're gonna stick
a knife in their back.

89
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:17,450
I had to wait till some stupid foster home
losers took me, and then I slipped.

90
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:19,150
- Maybe you ain't
as smart as us.

91
00:07:19,150 --> 00:07:20,750
- Oh, eat it.
- I am.

92
00:07:21,350 --> 00:07:23,200
I just want
my own place.

93
00:07:23,250 --> 00:07:24,700
Like an apartment
or something.

94
00:07:24,700 --> 00:07:26,700
Yeah, right.
You and me, man,

95
00:07:26,750 --> 00:07:28,200
We'll hook up
with someone.

96
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:31,600
With my brains and your
wonderful personality, we'll be rich.

97
00:07:35,900 --> 00:07:38,210
Get outta here!
Go, go, go!

98
00:07:44,150 --> 00:07:45,500
Let's split up!

99
00:07:45,900 --> 00:07:47,750
- See you, guys!
- All right. Bye!

100
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:53,200
This way!

101
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:01,000
Come on!

102
00:08:01,150 --> 00:08:03,000
Go, go, go, man!

103
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,510
Go, man! This way.

104
00:08:04,510 --> 00:08:06,610
Come on, come on!
Come on! Go!

105
00:08:07,250 --> 00:08:08,250
Quick! Go!

106
00:08:08,300 --> 00:08:09,900
Quick, quick, quick!
Move!

107
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:17,000
- Uhh!
- Down here.

108
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:21,550
Right here.

109
00:08:22,130 --> 00:08:23,950
Shut it.
Quick, quick, quick!

110
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:37,000
Check it out, man.

111
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:20,820
Perry?

112
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:40,110
Aah!

113
00:09:55,100 --> 00:09:56,750
What is that?

114
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:18,450
Wow!

115
00:10:22,250 --> 00:10:24,900
Jesse, cops!
Run!

116
00:10:27,800 --> 00:10:28,500
There he is!

117
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:30,100
Hold it, kid!

118
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:36,250
Heading up the stairs, Jim!

119
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:40,650
Hey, kid!

120
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:43,350
- All right.
- Hold on.

121
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:44,350
Let go of me!

122
00:10:45,300 --> 00:10:46,400
Relax.

123
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:47,700
Calm down.

124
00:10:47,700 --> 00:10:48,700
Unhh! Uhh! No!

125
00:10:54,550 --> 00:10:56,620
Breakin' and enterin', malicious mischief,

126
00:10:56,620 --> 00:10:58,660
Vandalism, resisting arrest.

127
00:10:59,450 --> 00:11:01,120
Anything else happen
I should know about?

128
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:03,000
Yeah, I robbed a few banks.
Is that a problem?

129
00:11:03,100 --> 00:11:04,730
Yeah, I'm glad you were
only out there 3 days, son.

130
00:11:04,730 --> 00:11:05,400
Sit down.

131
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:06,950
Aw, did you miss me,
Dwight?

132
00:11:07,350 --> 00:11:09,000
So was Perry with you
on this number?

133
00:11:09,100 --> 00:11:10,350
Perry who?

134
00:11:10,450 --> 00:11:11,550
Look, don't play.

135
00:11:11,550 --> 00:11:13,300
Don't come in here
being a bonehead.

136
00:11:13,300 --> 00:11:14,700
Now, I hate telephones,

137
00:11:14,700 --> 00:11:17,300
and I spent 45 minutes
on a conference call...

138
00:11:17,300 --> 00:11:19,450
with the police department
and that Adventure Park...

139
00:11:19,450 --> 00:11:21,250
trying to keep you clean, son.

140
00:11:21,250 --> 00:11:23,300
You know what?
We were lucky this time.

141
00:11:23,300 --> 00:11:24,900
I kept you a little
behind out of court.

142
00:11:25,150 --> 00:11:28,000
You have to clean up the mess you made
at Northwestern Adventure Park.

143
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:31,550
Ah, ah,..., ah!  That is your probation.
You got a problem with that?

144
00:11:31,550 --> 00:11:33,400
- Yeah. Why should I have to clean it up?
- You know, I don't know why...

145
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:35,150
I fool around with
you kids in the first place.

146
00:11:35,160 --> 00:11:37,750
You know, I don't know why
I'm working so much overtime with you.

147
00:11:37,750 --> 00:11:41,750
But you split out again here,
and I am out of the picture.  Gone!

148
00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:45,900
You'll be with Youth Authority,
court supervised and controlled.

149
00:11:45,900 --> 00:11:50,500
They'll put you in baby jail. That means
a lockup in juvenile hall, son.

150
00:12:00,100 --> 00:12:01,750
Ok, look...

151
00:12:02,300 --> 00:12:04,600
Your placement is still on.
The greenwoods are OK.

152
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:07,100
They don't even care
about this...incident.

153
00:12:07,100 --> 00:12:08,530
What's wrong with  them?

154
00:12:08,750 --> 00:12:09,750
Oh, I see.

155
00:12:09,800 --> 00:12:13,000
Because they want you in their home, there's
got to be something wrong with them, right?

156
00:12:13,050 --> 00:12:14,450
What do you think?

157
00:12:15,670 --> 00:12:20,000
I think that on paper you're still real
young, so you get some chances.

158
00:12:20,150 --> 00:12:22,950
Not an infinite number of chances,
but a few.

159
00:12:23,010 --> 00:12:24,700
A few, son.

160
00:12:24,850 --> 00:12:26,200
You get it?

161
00:12:33,450 --> 00:12:36,750
Ok, you got any questions
about, uh, any of this?

162
00:12:36,900 --> 00:12:38,600
You hear from my mom?

163
00:12:38,900 --> 00:12:40,850
You still want me
to hear from you mom?

164
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:43,400
I just want to know if she's okay.

165
00:12:45,030 --> 00:12:48,150
Nobody's heard from your mom
in six years, Jesse.

166
00:13:13,300 --> 00:13:15,330
Anytime you're ready, big guy.

167
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:19,650
Hi, Jesse.
Hi, Dwight.

168
00:13:19,650 --> 00:13:21,600
- Hey, how are you doing, Annie?
- Good.  How you doing?

169
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:23,900
Well, It's kinda been a long day
for the both of us.

170
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:26,500
- Hello, Dwight.
- Hey.

171
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:28,900
Hey.
There he is.

172
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:35,000
- Can I carry your stuff for you?
- No.

173
00:13:36,450 --> 00:13:40,530
Well, why don't we go inside and
wash up, and we'll have dinner?

174
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:47,900
Well, Glen, got a little
paperwork here for you.

175
00:13:48,450 --> 00:13:50,800
Always got to have
the paperwork.

176
00:13:51,100 --> 00:13:55,250
You know, I bought a new car recently.
Man, with the contracts and all, it came to 37 pages.

177
00:13:56,450 --> 00:13:59,100
Well, this is a lease.
I ain't buying yet.

178
00:14:00,500 --> 00:14:02,900
- You interested in computers, Jesse?
- No.

179
00:14:03,200 --> 00:14:06,400
- Well, I could teach you.
I just learned last summer myself.
- I'm not into it.

180
00:14:07,350 --> 00:14:08,700
That makes two of us.

181
00:14:08,900 --> 00:14:10,330
Well, I wasn't, either,...

182
00:14:10,330 --> 00:14:14,100
but then I decided that I wanted
a second career as a journalist.

183
00:14:14,100 --> 00:14:15,100
I'm a teacher,

184
00:14:15,700 --> 00:14:20,000
and so I'm taking
the Summer off to write.

185
00:14:20,100 --> 00:14:23,600
A couple of weeklies have, uh,
taken a couple of my stories.

186
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:27,650
- I haven't earned anything yet.
- Go ahead!  Just dig right in.

187
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:34,250
In fact, that's how I know Dwight.
I did a story on Cooperton.

188
00:14:34,500 --> 00:14:35,700
Dwight's a jerk.

189
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:42,800
So, what exactly
are you into, Jesse?

190
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:44,800
I'm not into talking
while I'm eating.

191
00:15:06,100 --> 00:15:07,800
Here's your room, Jesse.

192
00:15:10,330 --> 00:15:11,800
Our bedroom's downstairs,

193
00:15:11,800 --> 00:15:12,900
buut, uh...

194
00:15:12,900 --> 00:15:16,200
You've got the best view
in the house.

195
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:19,040
Go ahead. Open it.

196
00:15:19,040 --> 00:15:22,480
It's, uh, kind
of a welcome gift.

197
00:15:22,950 --> 00:15:25,480
You can open it
later, if you like.

198
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:30,000
Uh, I--I bought you
some things, some clothes.

199
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:34,450
Some socks, and, uh,
there's lots of blue.

200
00:15:34,850 --> 00:15:36,400
Dwight said you like blue.

201
00:15:38,800 --> 00:15:40,700
Anyway, uh,
try them on,

202
00:15:40,700 --> 00:15:43,500
And... And if you don't like them,
we can exchange them.

203
00:15:54,300 --> 00:15:55,550
Well, I guess we'll get outta here now.

204
00:15:55,550 --> 00:15:58,000
If you need us for anything,
we'll be downstairs.

205
00:15:58,000 --> 00:15:59,450
Good night, Jesse.

206
00:15:59,450 --> 00:16:02,650
It's great to have you here, Jesse.
Good night.

207
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:47,000
Hey, Jess.  You remember that turn
right before the bridge?  That's 88th Street.

208
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:50,400
My garage is
straight up from there.

209
00:16:50,750 --> 00:16:53,550
If you go 6 more blocks,
you'll be right at the house.

210
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:55,100
Think you can find it?

211
00:16:56,500 --> 00:17:00,650
When you go inside, you're looking for
the Aquatic Theater. Ask for Randolph.

212
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:07,990
Yeah. Great.

213
00:17:44,500 --> 00:17:45,700
Hey, mister.

214
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:49,000
Do you know where
I can find Randolph?

215
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:51,000
Yeah, he lives in the cottage
right by the water.

216
00:17:52,300 --> 00:17:53,200
Thanks.

217
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:13,350
Hello?

218
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:15,100
Randolph?

219
00:18:19,100 --> 00:18:20,200
Randolph?

220
00:18:36,500 --> 00:18:37,900
What's this?

221
00:18:49,050 --> 00:18:50,100
Well...

222
00:18:50,500 --> 00:18:52,500
The artist returns.

223
00:18:52,600 --> 00:18:55,000
Well come back.

224
00:18:59,900 --> 00:19:03,000
We've all become great admirers
of your work around here...

225
00:19:03,700 --> 00:19:07,000
...but all good things
must come to an end.

226
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:11,700
Time to let your
creativity flow backwards.

227
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:13,450
You know what to do
with all this?

228
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:18,900
- Yes, I do.
- Good.  See you later.

229
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:36,800
Wow!

230
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:19,000
Hey!
Uhh!

231
00:20:19,830 --> 00:20:21,500
What are you doing up here?

232
00:20:22,400 --> 00:20:24,430
Nothing.

233
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:32,000
7,000 pounds, that one.

234
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:35,000
Jaws powerful enough
to crush bones to oatmeal.

235
00:20:35,150 --> 00:20:36,250
Willy gets into moods.

236
00:20:36,250 --> 00:20:38,650
You gotta give him his space.
You know what I mean?

237
00:20:38,900 --> 00:20:42,300
Don't bother him, he won't bother you.
You understand?

238
00:20:42,450 --> 00:20:43,450
Sure.

239
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:57,800
[band music plays]

240
00:21:04,940 --> 00:21:07,000
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
girls and boys,...</i>

241
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:10,000
<i>...just a reminder that our sea lion show
plays 4 times daily,</i>

242
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:12,900
<i>...and your Northwest Adventure Pass
will admit you to all sessions.</i>

243
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:16,500
<i>Show times are at 10:00,
12:00, 2:00, and 4:00.</i>

244
00:21:16,500 --> 00:21:19,990
[crowd applauds]

245
00:21:22,100 --> 00:21:25,400
<i>As you can see, Olivia and Belinda
flip out at lunchtime.</i>

246
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:29,850
Belinda. Belinda, we have a nice-looking
audience.  What do you think?

247
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:32,000
[barking]

248
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:38,500
Yes.

249
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:52,550
You are looking so beautiful.
How about a kiss?

250
00:21:58,100 --> 00:22:00,800
You should be ashamed
of yourselves.

251
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:05,000
Wave goodbye to everybody.
Wave goodbye.

252
00:22:05,400 --> 00:22:08,350
<i>Let's give a big round of applause
to Olivia and Belinda,</i>

253
00:22:08,350 --> 00:22:10,750
<i>...and their trainer, Rae Lindley.</i>

254
00:22:10,750 --> 00:22:11,900
[applause]

255
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:17,100
<i>In a couple of minutes, ladies and gentlemen,
you'll be able to have a look at Willy,</i>

256
00:22:17,100 --> 00:22:20,650
<i>...our prize orca whale,
right here in the main tank.</i>

257
00:22:42,200 --> 00:22:45,100
- You're the graffiti kid, aren't you?
- I guess.

