00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:49,000
You really messed up
our observation area.

259
00:22:49,750 --> 00:22:51,450
Sorry.

260
00:22:54,700 --> 00:22:56,650
- You like whales?
- I like him.

261
00:22:56,900 --> 00:23:00,000
Well, he doesn't like anybody,
so you be careful around him.

262
00:23:00,100 --> 00:23:01,550
See, Willy's a case.

263
00:23:01,900 --> 00:23:03,900
A very special case.

264
00:23:04,250 --> 00:23:05,500
So?

265
00:23:05,850 --> 00:23:07,500
Who isn't?

266
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:31,500
Wanna play catch?

267
00:23:31,900 --> 00:23:33,100
Catch?

268
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:34,250
Yeah.

269
00:23:34,350 --> 00:23:37,500
I like to throw the ball
around once in a while.

270
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:40,510
Had this mitt ever since
I was in eighth grade.

271
00:23:40,800 --> 00:23:45,300
We used to sit around and...
Spit in it, Smack it.

272
00:23:45,800 --> 00:23:48,850
Get a nice pocket there.
Look at that.  Pretty nice, huh?

273
00:23:48,900 --> 00:23:50,000
Let's play.

274
00:23:50,400 --> 00:23:53,000
How much they paying
you to be my jailer?

275
00:23:58,600 --> 00:24:00,250
Your jailer, huh?

276
00:24:01,160 --> 00:24:05,000
Yeah, boy, I'm making such a great deal
on you, you wouldn't believe it.

277
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:07,000
You're
a regular cash cow, kid.

278
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:11,000
That, plus a million dollars, I could
probably retire by the time I'm 300 years old.

279
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:14,350
Look, you're gonna have to help
me out a little bit here.

280
00:24:14,750 --> 00:24:15,480
Ok?

281
00:24:16,750 --> 00:24:19,650
Dwight says that I'm supposed
to make some rules for you, and....

282
00:24:19,800 --> 00:24:24,450
Problem is, I've always been a better rule-breaker
than a rule-maker myself, and, uh....

283
00:24:25,100 --> 00:24:27,450
So you're gonna have to tell me
what you think you need.

284
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:29,400
You're askin' me?

285
00:24:29,500 --> 00:24:31,800
Yeah! Well, you're
the big expert, right?

286
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:33,350
I Don't know any rules.

287
00:24:33,350 --> 00:24:37,000
Aw, come on!  Kid like you?
Been around, been in trouble.

288
00:24:38,100 --> 00:24:39,600
What's it gonna be?

289
00:24:40,350 --> 00:24:42,000
Ok.

290
00:24:42,400 --> 00:24:43,800
Let's see. Uh...

291
00:24:46,400 --> 00:24:48,600
I got it.
First rule is...

292
00:24:48,700 --> 00:24:51,000
You have to give me an allowance
every week.

293
00:24:52,800 --> 00:24:54,350
Fiive bucks.

294
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:56,150
What's next?

295
00:24:56,700 --> 00:24:58,900
I don't know.
I haven't thought about it yet.

296
00:25:01,100 --> 00:25:04,650
Well, while you're thinking about it,
I need you in bed every night by 10:00 o'clock.

297
00:25:05,400 --> 00:25:07,750
And up every morning
in time for breakfast.

298
00:25:09,150 --> 00:25:12,450
And I want you in the house
every night by 7:00.

299
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:13,900
And don't go running
around the neighborhood

300
00:25:13,900 --> 00:25:15,650
...and disappearing without
telling somebody.

301
00:25:15,650 --> 00:25:17,500
'cause we need to know
where you are.

302
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:19,150
Ok!

303
00:25:30,750 --> 00:25:33,250
Kid.

304
00:25:56,300 --> 00:25:57,650
[sighs]

305
00:25:59,900 --> 00:26:01,900
Almost finished with this place.

306
00:26:17,220 --> 00:26:19,600
[music]

307
00:26:30,950 --> 00:26:32,000
Ohh!

308
00:26:33,900 --> 00:26:35,000
[music]

309
00:26:43,350 --> 00:26:45,000
Come on. Come on.

310
00:27:51,400 --> 00:27:52,070
Aah!

311
00:27:53,750 --> 00:27:55,400
Ha ha!

312
00:27:55,450 --> 00:27:58,000
Well, you have a nice
day, too, grouch.

313
00:28:02,300 --> 00:28:04,750
He likes messing around with
people's heads, doesn't he?

314
00:28:04,850 --> 00:28:06,250
Yes, he does.

315
00:28:06,800 --> 00:28:09,900
If I can't get him to perform,
no one can.

316
00:28:10,200 --> 00:28:12,300
Orcas are usually
nice and smart.

317
00:28:12,300 --> 00:28:14,450
Willy's smart and nasty.

318
00:28:17,500 --> 00:28:20,850
- You really like him, huh?
- Yeah.

319
00:28:21,300 --> 00:28:24,500
Good.
You can help me out.

320
00:28:29,800 --> 00:28:31,500
Broken belly.  Toss it.

321
00:28:31,750 --> 00:28:34,000
Look. This is a good fish.

322
00:28:34,800 --> 00:28:38,000
That's a bad fish.
Good fish, bad fish.

323
00:28:39,700 --> 00:28:43,500
Every day we gotta sort out what Willy can eat
from the cheap crap they buy him.

324
00:28:43,690 --> 00:28:46,500
Willy's a killer whale, right?

325
00:28:46,550 --> 00:28:47,650
So would he kill us?

326
00:28:48,200 --> 00:28:51,800
No!  Orcas are just hunters.
Mostly they eat fish.

327
00:28:52,050 --> 00:28:56,900
Well, sometimes they'll eat
porpoises, squid... birds...

328
00:28:57,100 --> 00:28:58,100
...sharks...

329
00:28:58,400 --> 00:29:00,900
What Willy really
likes is salmon.

330
00:29:01,800 --> 00:29:03,300
That's his chocolate.

331
00:29:07,900 --> 00:29:11,450
Kiss me. Kiss me. Kiss me.
Rrr...Rrr...

332
00:29:12,800 --> 00:29:14,750
Ready to get back
to your painting?

333
00:29:38,300 --> 00:29:42,250
[music]

334
00:30:02,570 --> 00:30:04,300
Aah!

335
00:31:14,800 --> 00:31:16,200
[cough]

336
00:31:29,450 --> 00:31:31,350
You saved my life.

337
00:31:43,750 --> 00:31:46,650
You must have something special, kid.
That's why Willy didn't eat you up.

338
00:31:46,700 --> 00:31:49,100
- What do you mean?
- Oh, I don't know.

339
00:31:49,200 --> 00:31:51,900
High blood, medicine roots.

340
00:31:51,900 --> 00:31:54,550
- No way.
- Then you're one lucky white boy.

341
00:31:54,550 --> 00:31:56,000
Like the sound
of that better?

342
00:31:56,000 --> 00:31:59,800
Willy doesn't have a problem with me.
We appreciate each other.

343
00:31:59,800 --> 00:32:01,650
Appreciate? Ha.

344
00:32:01,730 --> 00:32:03,300
Willy saved your butt.

345
00:32:03,600 --> 00:32:06,900
I don't know why everybody around
here has a big problem with him just because...

346
00:32:06,900 --> 00:32:09,100
Willy does not like visitors
in his tank.

347
00:32:09,300 --> 00:32:11,000
What the heck
were you doing there?

348
00:32:11,650 --> 00:32:13,000
