349
00:32:13,850 --> 00:32:16,250
Job was almost up.

350
00:32:17,250 --> 00:32:19,000
Didn't want to say good-bye.

351
00:32:21,200 --> 00:32:22,000
Well, just maybe...

352
00:32:22,950 --> 00:32:24,750
- What?
- Ahh!

353
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:26,650
Old Indian stuff.

354
00:32:33,850 --> 00:32:35,000
Orcas.

355
00:32:35,650 --> 00:32:37,900
Ever look into Willy’s eyes?

356
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:41,350
Those eyes discovered the stars

357
00:32:41,650 --> 00:32:44,330
...long before man was even
a whisper on mother earth.

358
00:32:45,500 --> 00:32:48,150
Could look into a man's soul
if they want.

359
00:32:48,400 --> 00:32:49,900
Willy...

360
00:32:50,090 --> 00:32:52,650
He won't look at Rae...or me.

361
00:32:54,500 --> 00:32:56,350
Maybe he sees you.

362
00:33:05,200 --> 00:33:07,200
Looks like your parents
are still up.

363
00:33:07,200 --> 00:33:08,900
They're not my parents.

364
00:33:12,700 --> 00:33:14,450
Jesse, where have you been?

365
00:33:15,150 --> 00:33:16,550
You're soaked!

366
00:33:16,550 --> 00:33:17,700
I was at work.

367
00:33:17,700 --> 00:33:20,650
You snuck out of the house in the
middle of the night to clean up graffiti?

368
00:33:20,950 --> 00:33:23,400
- That's an amazing story.
- I fell in the tank.

369
00:33:23,400 --> 00:33:25,000
The whale tank?

370
00:33:25,350 --> 00:33:28,300
Will somebody please tell me
what the heck is going on around here?

371
00:33:28,300 --> 00:33:30,550
I slipped and fell in the tank.
It's my fault.

372
00:33:30,550 --> 00:33:33,600
- Oh, right.
- Folks, my name is Randolph.

373
00:33:34,750 --> 00:33:36,800
Randolph, how are you?
I'm Glen. This is my wife Annie.

374
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:38,000
Hi.

375
00:33:38,100 --> 00:33:41,750
I've been supervising Jesse down at
the park.  He's been doing a really good job.

376
00:33:41,800 --> 00:33:45,300
Did his cleanup, helped out in some
other areas, and made some friends.

377
00:33:45,480 --> 00:33:49,650
The thing is, we could use him for the rest
of the summer, if that's all right with you.

378
00:33:49,750 --> 00:33:52,650
Make a job of it.
Pay him a little something, too.

379
00:33:53,350 --> 00:33:54,400
What do you say
to that?

380
00:33:54,400 --> 00:33:56,650
Yeah! Yeah!
I want to, please!

381
00:33:56,820 --> 00:33:59,000
Finally found something
that you're into, huh, Jess?

382
00:34:00,200 --> 00:34:04,130
Well, it sounds OK, but days.
No more of this sneaking out at night.

383
00:34:04,150 --> 00:34:06,000
All right.
I promise I won't.

384
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:08,450
Just be straight with us
from now on, all right?

385
00:34:08,550 --> 00:34:11,000
If there's something
that you need, just ask us.

386
00:34:11,250 --> 00:34:12,650
Think you can do that?

387
00:34:13,600 --> 00:34:15,350
All right.
It's past your bedtime.

388
00:34:15,350 --> 00:34:17,450
I think you should get in
the house, son.

389
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:19,650
I'm not your son.

390
00:34:24,350 --> 00:34:26,300
Yeah, I know that.

391
00:34:45,450 --> 00:34:48,100
[Willy crying out]

392
00:34:54,300 --> 00:34:55,750
- Ok, easy!
- Watch it!  Watch it!

393
00:34:56,000 --> 00:34:57,100
Watch those lines!

394
00:34:57,100 --> 00:34:58,900
[Willy cries out]

395
00:35:00,800 --> 00:35:01,950
Why don't you just
get out of the way?

396
00:35:02,700 --> 00:35:03,650
I'm not in the way.

397
00:35:05,400 --> 00:35:08,000
Look, this examination area
is completely inadequate.

398
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:09,750
But it's all we've got.

399
00:35:09,750 --> 00:35:13,350
Holding him in this net is dangerous.  We've
told you that I don't know how many times.

400
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:16,850
- Could you finish the exam now?
- No. He's acting up too much.

401
00:35:16,850 --> 00:35:19,700
You and Dial bought Willy
from some slimeball whale catcher.

402
00:35:19,700 --> 00:35:22,500
He was too big and too old to be caught
in the first place.

403
00:35:22,500 --> 00:35:24,850
Then you put him
in a dolphin tank, alone.

404
00:35:24,850 --> 00:35:27,580
He's not a natural performer,
and you expect me to work miracles?

405
00:35:27,600 --> 00:35:29,750
You're paid to train him,
not analyze him.

406
00:35:29,750 --> 00:35:32,700
These are not the circumstances
described when I signed on.

407
00:35:32,800 --> 00:35:36,300
You're a professional, right?
So make it work.

408
00:35:39,400 --> 00:35:41,700
Dial give me a line,
and I am not gonna cross it.

409
00:35:41,700 --> 00:35:43,670
This is not about crossing lines.

410
00:35:43,800 --> 00:35:45,900
Which words don't you understand?

411
00:35:45,900 --> 00:35:48,000
Look, if the whale was
to bring in customers...

412
00:35:48,350 --> 00:35:50,000
[crying out]

413
00:35:50,400 --> 00:35:51,900
Then we could spend
some money on him.

414
00:35:51,900 --> 00:35:55,300
But since he's not, you're just gonna
have to make do with what you've got.

415
00:35:56,020 --> 00:35:58,650
Easy, Willy!  Easy, son!

416
00:35:59,650 --> 00:36:01,850
Untie those back lines!

417
00:36:06,900 --> 00:36:09,650
What's going on?
Randolph, what happened?

418
00:36:09,650 --> 00:36:11,650
I don't know.
The net came loose.

419
00:36:20,400 --> 00:36:21,850
I saw what you did.

420
00:36:21,850 --> 00:36:23,750
- So?
- So nothing.

421
00:36:24,900 --> 00:36:27,000
I'm sure Willy’s grateful.

422
00:36:35,900 --> 00:36:38,350
The whale's still not performing.
We're getting deeper into this,...

423
00:36:38,600 --> 00:36:40,900
...and Rae keeps saying we have
to expand that tank.

424
00:36:40,900 --> 00:36:42,700
Very nice.
This is what I get...

425
00:36:42,700 --> 00:36:44,500
...for bringing the animal in
to boost business.

426
00:36:44,850 --> 00:36:47,750
Why don't we just move him into the
Ritz-Carlton?  I can tack it onto the 5,000...

427
00:36:47,750 --> 00:36:49,900
I just dumped into his
latest insurance premium.

428
00:36:50,200 --> 00:36:53,100
Yeah. The whale's worth
more dead than alive.

429
00:36:54,000 --> 00:36:56,600
It will cost at least 100,000...

430
00:36:56,600 --> 00:36:59,410
...to expand that psychotic
malcontent's playpen.

431
00:37:00,450 --> 00:37:03,400
Oh, God,
I hate that whale.

432
00:37:22,700 --> 00:37:24,950
You got any leftover
scraps or anything...

433
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:27,250
...I could take your hands off?

434
00:37:27,250 --> 00:37:28,540
Might have.

435
00:37:28,800 --> 00:37:30,750
Well, I've got a really
special friend named Willy.

436
00:37:31,310 --> 00:37:33,200
Why would he
want scraps?

437
00:37:33,200 --> 00:37:37,550
- Well... He's a whale.
- A whale?

438
00:37:43,850 --> 00:37:45,150
Jess, man.

439
00:37:45,200 --> 00:37:47,000
I'll meet you all up there.

440
00:37:47,400 --> 00:37:49,250
- What's up, man?
 - Perry.

441
00:37:49,250 --> 00:37:51,250
New clothes.  New gig?

442
00:37:51,250 --> 00:37:53,770
- Staying with some people.
- It's cool.

443
00:37:54,300 --> 00:37:56,750
What happened to you that night, man?
I saw you get popped.

444
00:37:56,750 --> 00:37:59,500
Not much.
Had to clean up all my mess.

445
00:37:59,600 --> 00:38:01,440
I'm working there now.

446
00:38:01,600 --> 00:38:03,150
They looking for me?

447
00:38:03,400 --> 00:38:05,150
- Nah.
- Cool.

448
00:38:05,450 --> 00:38:08,500
Yeah, it's a total drag, man.
Sorry.

449
00:38:08,700 --> 00:38:11,200
No sweat.
Where you been staying?

450
00:38:11,350 --> 00:38:12,550
Dayton set me up.

451
00:38:12,650 --> 00:38:16,250
Working for him now, looking out
for cops and stuff. You know?

452
00:38:16,450 --> 00:38:20,300
I mentioned you to him.
I can hook you up if you want.

453
00:38:22,500 --> 00:38:25,000
I gotta think about that.

454
00:38:25,100 --> 00:38:26,500
Snooze, you lose.

455
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:28,750
Stop by sometime, huh?

456
00:38:29,000 --> 00:38:30,500
See you around.
I gotta bail.

457
00:38:30,500 --> 00:38:31,650
All right, man.

458
00:38:32,700 --> 00:38:34,650
- See ya.
- Later.

459
00:39:02,700 --> 00:39:05,000
[music]

460
00:39:17,650 --> 00:39:19,000
What's the matter, Willy?

461
00:39:19,000 --> 00:39:21,950
Thought you liked these things.
You know?

462
00:39:23,000 --> 00:39:26,450
Well, you know.  You're supposed
to eat it like this.

463
00:39:28,900 --> 00:39:30,000
See?

464
00:39:34,800 --> 00:39:36,290
No?

465
00:39:38,060 --> 00:39:42,770
Oh...You want me to put it
in your mouth.

466
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:49,450
I'll make a deal
with you.

467
00:39:50,880 --> 00:39:56,450
Don't bite my hand off, and I'll
give you the fish. Ok?

468
00:40:05,000 --> 00:40:06,900
You like these.

469
00:40:53,000 --> 00:40:54,600
Wow.

470
00:41:03,800 --> 00:41:06,000
You're like... rubbery.

471
00:41:07,200 --> 00:41:09,150
Skin peels off.

472
00:41:09,800 --> 00:41:12,500
Still a beautiful animal, though.

473
00:41:12,600 --> 00:41:15,950
Well, buddy, I gotta go.

474
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:20,450
We'll save these scraps
and fishes for later.

475
00:41:35,100 --> 00:41:37,650
What, you want
to go with me?

476
00:41:44,800 --> 00:41:47,000
Oh, I can do that, too.

477
00:41:50,700 --> 00:41:52,870
You do it with the other arm?
Yeah?

478
00:41:53,500 --> 00:41:56,000
You do it with the other arm?

479
00:41:56,800 --> 00:41:58,800
Hey!

480
00:42:00,000 --> 00:42:02,200
Hey, can you wave?

481
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:08,300
Can you dance for me?

482
00:42:08,400 --> 00:42:10,800
Can you groove?

483
00:42:10,900 --> 00:42:12,000
Dance?

484
00:42:12,000 --> 00:42:14,200
Rae.

485
00:42:14,300 --> 00:42:16,350
What?

486
00:42:16,800 --> 00:42:18,600
Can you go in circles?

487
00:42:18,600 --> 00:42:20,000
Hey, look.

488
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:27,300
Hey. You're really doing it.

489
00:42:27,500 --> 00:42:29,510
Yeah, look at you.

490
00:42:31,700 --> 00:42:32,750
Makes me dizzy.

491
00:42:32,800 --> 00:42:36,080
Looks like Willy’s
got himself a soul mate.

492
00:42:48,900 --> 00:42:50,000
Jess.

493
00:42:52,000 --> 00:42:53,000
Can you feed him?

494
00:42:53,100 --> 00:42:54,750
Sure, I can feed him.

495
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:01,500
It's easy.

496
00:43:07,400 --> 00:43:08,400
Want a try?

497
00:43:11,000 --> 00:43:12,100
Come on.

498
00:43:25,700 --> 00:43:28,150
Willy and I didn't get off
to a very good start.

499
00:43:28,500 --> 00:43:32,450
He thinks I'm the wicked witch or something
'cause of the medical tests I had to do on him.

500
00:43:34,350 --> 00:43:38,550
You know, out in the ocean, killer whales
like Willy live in families. pods.

501
00:43:38,800 --> 00:43:41,500
Some of them spend their whole lives with
their moms, and they never leave them.

502
00:43:41,500 --> 00:43:42,000
Never?

503
00:43:42,000 --> 00:43:44,950
Nope. Their social structure is
really important to them.

504
00:43:45,350 --> 00:43:48,100
Over 50 orcas have been
seen traveling together.

505
00:43:48,100 --> 00:43:50,450
Some of them stay together forever,
for their whole lives.

506
00:43:50,700 --> 00:43:51,800
You've seen them out there?

507
00:43:51,800 --> 00:43:53,400
Yeah. My dad was in the Navy.

508
00:43:53,700 --> 00:43:55,400
He did sonar research
on whales.

509
00:43:55,500 --> 00:43:57,550
I went out there all the time.

510
00:43:57,800 --> 00:43:59,600
Well, do you do research here?

511
00:44:00,000 --> 00:44:03,400
No. Here, I'm just a trainer, but
I want to work out on the ocean.

512
00:44:05,200 --> 00:44:08,600
I'm going back to school
to get my PhD. in marine biology.

513
00:44:08,880 --> 00:44:14,550
