00:53:05,970 --> 00:53:07,800
Hey, Jesse, what's up?

641
00:53:07,800 --> 00:53:09,150
Annie.  Dinner.

642
00:53:09,150 --> 00:53:11,200
Oh, terrific.

643
00:53:11,200 --> 00:53:12,850
Hold on
one second.

644
00:53:13,000 --> 00:53:15,750
I need 2 sets of gaskets for that, too.
So, don't forget.

645
00:53:15,750 --> 00:53:17,650
Bring them in first thing
in the morning?

646
00:53:18,000 --> 00:53:19,500
All right. Thanks.

647
00:53:20,850 --> 00:53:24,450
Oh, neat car!
Check it out!

648
00:53:24,450 --> 00:53:26,200
- You like that car?
- Oh, yeah.

649
00:53:26,200 --> 00:53:27,300
That's a classic.

650
00:53:28,000 --> 00:53:29,900
It was the love
of my life.

651
00:53:31,300 --> 00:53:36,000
I spent 1 1/2 years putting that baby
together, getting it in primo condition.

652
00:53:36,650 --> 00:53:38,000
And then I had to sell it.

653
00:53:38,300 --> 00:53:39,000
Why?

654
00:53:40,500 --> 00:53:45,750
Well, simple reason that you can't have
more than one love in your life.

655
00:53:47,600 --> 00:53:50,000
Oh, yeah?

656
00:53:50,200 --> 00:53:51,700
Yeah.

657
00:53:53,300 --> 00:53:56,650
You and Annie...

658
00:53:56,900 --> 00:53:58,600
Ever fight?

659
00:53:59,300 --> 00:54:03,450
Yeah. We, uh...schedule one
every other month or so.

660
00:54:05,800 --> 00:54:06,600
Why?

661
00:54:07,000 --> 00:54:08,800
Just asking.

662
00:54:10,800 --> 00:54:16,000
- Oh.  What's this?
- That's a picture of me and my mother.

663
00:54:16,000 --> 00:54:17,350
Long time ago.

664
00:54:17,650 --> 00:54:19,100
About your age there.

665
00:54:20,000 --> 00:54:21,450
So where is she now?

666
00:54:21,800 --> 00:54:25,120
Well...She died about 2 years ago.

667
00:54:26,250 --> 00:54:29,250
Yeah, well, my mom's coming
to get me one of these days.

668
00:54:30,650 --> 00:54:31,630
She is?

669
00:54:32,300 --> 00:54:33,800
Not too long from now.

670
00:54:34,900 --> 00:54:38,650
Well, that's funny.  That's, uh....
That's not what they said.

671
00:54:41,100 --> 00:54:42,570
You don't believe me, do you?

672
00:54:45,100 --> 00:54:48,800
It's not that.  I just...was
under the impression that--

673
00:54:48,800 --> 00:54:52,000
I don't care what those people said.
Those people don't know anything!

674
00:54:54,700 --> 00:54:57,000
Ok.
Ok.

