we should call Dwight.

681
00:55:19,200 --> 00:55:20,500
It's after 11:00.

682
00:55:20,500 --> 00:55:22,700
I know what time it is!

683
00:55:24,200 --> 00:55:26,000
I'm sorry.

684
00:55:26,400 --> 00:55:27,500
Jesse?

685
00:55:27,800 --> 00:55:28,450
Where have you been?

686
00:55:28,450 --> 00:55:31,400
What do you think you're doing?
You weren't at the park.

687
00:55:31,460 --> 00:55:33,300
You're supposed to let us know
where you are! Remember?

688
00:55:33,350 --> 00:55:35,450
It doesn't matter.
You want to dump me?

689
00:55:35,450 --> 00:55:37,060
Go ahead. I Don't care.
I'm not living here.

690
00:55:37,060 --> 00:55:39,200
I'm just staying here for a while.

691
00:55:46,300 --> 00:55:46,900
[door slams]

692
00:55:46,900 --> 00:55:48,200
How do you like that?

693
00:55:48,800 --> 00:55:50,450
Just when you think you're starting
to get through,

694
00:55:50,500 --> 00:55:54,000
...starting to make some sense,
starting to make a connection...

695
00:55:54,650 --> 00:55:55,650
Whammo!

696
00:55:55,650 --> 00:55:58,000
Well, he's scared.
He's pushing us away.

697
00:55:58,000 --> 00:55:59,750
I'd like to give him a
push right out the door.

698
00:55:59,750 --> 00:56:01,700
Hey, don't say things
like that!

699
00:56:01,700 --> 00:56:02,650
What's the matter?
Does that make you angry?

700
00:56:02,650 --> 00:56:04,000
Yes, it makes me angry!  It didn't help...

701
00:56:04,000 --> 00:56:06,250
...if you use that tone of voice
the minute he came in the door.

702
00:56:06,400 --> 00:56:08,800
- He's driving me crazy!
- You know why you're really angry?

703
00:56:08,800 --> 00:56:09,330
No. Why?

704
00:56:09,330 --> 00:56:11,400
You want to know why?
Because you have feelings for him,

705
00:56:11,400 --> 00:56:14,200
...and that scares you because
he reminds you of yourself.

706
00:56:15,650 --> 00:56:17,400
- Ok. You're right.
- I know I'm right.

707
00:56:17,400 --> 00:56:20,400
I don't like it.  We don't
owe anybody anything, OK?

708
00:56:20,400 --> 00:56:24,210
We tried.  We did the best we could do.
It doesn't have to be any more than that.

709
00:56:25,400 --> 00:56:27,000
What is this, another
one of your crusades?

710
00:56:27,000 --> 00:56:31,550
This is not a crusade, Glen.
We're talking about a human being!

711
00:56:31,900 --> 00:56:34,500
Annie, I'm happy,
just you and me.

712
00:56:44,900 --> 00:56:45,500
Jesse?

713
00:56:45,500 --> 00:56:46,600
Are you OK?

714
00:56:55,600 --> 00:56:57,000
I just got scared.

715
00:57:00,300 --> 00:57:02,000
What are you scared about?

716
00:57:06,300 --> 00:57:07,250
I dn't know.

717
00:57:09,900 --> 00:57:11,530
I heard you guys fighting.

718
00:57:12,800 --> 00:57:14,110
It scared me.

719
00:57:20,250 --> 00:57:22,400
Jesse, adults
argue sometimes.

720
00:57:22,400 --> 00:57:25,350
But that doesn't mean that
anybody's gonna get hurt.

721
00:57:25,350 --> 00:57:27,000
I would never hurt Annie

722
00:57:27,100 --> 00:57:28,350
...or you.

723
00:57:29,100 --> 00:57:30,600
You should know that.

724
00:57:33,200 --> 00:57:34,250
I know.

725
00:57:45,500 --> 00:57:47,200
I see you opened
your present.

726
00:57:48,150 --> 00:57:49,500
Yeah. Thanks.

